👋 I have some new faces here that I wanted to say hi to, and I wanted to update my local peeps! 

My name is Erin Rodriguez, I’m a registered nurse in the state of Idaho and I’m a married mom of two handsome little devils! ☺️

I own and operate @goldenmedicalaesthetics and I’m very excited for our new expansion and to finally be able to delegate some of the many hats I wear.

Will Botox change my face?! 🫣

This is a common fear and question that I get during consultations and my response is always “no, you will still look like you just more youthful, rejuvenated, and refreshed.”

This is a perfect example of that. I adore this beautiful client of mine, and I am grateful for her to allow me to share her b + a. 
This is an angle that is mostly showcasing the before and after of her crows feet wrinkles after a Dysport treatment, but I purposefully captured a farther away shot so you can see that she still looks just like herself, she can still smile just the same, and her forehead looks so much smoother. Overall, she looks way more awake and rejuvenated. Beautiful in both photos, granted. ☺️

You, just shinier!! —

It’s been a minute for a good Dysport before + after! 😍 

Dysport is a neuromodulator that relaxes muscles that make wrinkles. In the simplest terminology 🤓 it’s kinda like crack though so be careful… once you go Dysport/Botox it’s HARD to go back! 😜

You’re so pretty pretty 🎶😘 really, she’s stunning. So naturally beautiful. The clients goal was to follow her natural shape, boost the top lip and enhance her cupids bow. 

Fun (not so fun) fact: I buy Hylenex (dissolver) on the regular! I’m always stocked up for 1. Safety and 2. If you’re a transfer client with old filler (especially lips) we’re starting over!

I don’t know what product the previous provider used, what techniques, or lack thereof. And there is usually migration visible from the outside and hidden within the mucosal region, when talking lips. Not all migration is totally injector related, sometimes rarely it just happens.. but either way.. We start over ok?! 😌

Though the process is longer, it ultimately gives you your best result, and the wait is worth it! 🤌🏼🫶🏼 —

My first Dysport B+A in the new space 😍 most new injectors think that Botox (tox) is the easy part and they’re scared of filler. (Been there too, many moons ago!)

In all actuality, Botox/Dysport/tox requires so much critical thought, palpation and anatomical knowledge before even picking up the syringe, to nail it just so; compared to the anatomical knowledge and artistic talent required to nail filler just so. In my humble opinion ☺️ it’s all multi-faceted, but in summary. 

Muscles are unique in how they present, animate, function, move, etc. I’m forever fascinated and obsessed with Tox!

It’s all the things, and I’m loving these results for this first timer. Just 40 units of Dysport to feel 5-10 years younger! Lol ✨—

Just 1 round for this beautiful gal! She’s 6 days post in photo 1 (still healing) 9 days post in photo 2. We are both thrilled and can’t wait for round 2 🤩 she will likely only need 2.

Have you ever wondered what getting your lips done looks like immediately after? This. This is it! 💋

1. ✨ She naturally has a fuller lower lip so we focused on building height and a cupids bow to her upper lip 
(Yes I did still do some symmetry correction + hydration to her lower lip, I never do just one lip).

2. ✨ Watch the video again and look at her eyes 👀 not only are they DREAMY, but we also did midface filler to brighten her eyes and soften her smile lines some. She could use more product, but we are starting here. At some point, you must address facial volume loss when adding more volume to your lips. It’s a harmonious pair. Less is always more, but it’s a must at some point! 

Typically, my clients don’t bruise or look too swollen after getting their lips done. It’s usually the day of or the morning after that’s the worst and it gets better from there. Swelling goes down 20-30% after you leave my chair.

So as long as you have a couple days off from work then that’s all you need! 😘 you can book with me through the link in my bio or text the office at 208-599-8860 📱 —
